# Teknovo DevOps Rule

## DO

- Confirm **deployment readiness** before any staging/production release
- Validate **environment**: secrets in host store only (`docs/SECRET_STORE.md`), never in repo
- Follow pipeline: **Build â†’ Test â†’ Fix (max 10 retries) â†’ Deploy â†’ Verify** (`.cursor/gates/execution/deployment-mode.md`)
- Produce **Deployment Impact Analysis** (Pillar 3) via `.cursor/skills/teknovo-devops-engineer/`
- Run Security **pre-deploy** review: `.cursor/skills/teknovo-security-review/`
- Use failure recovery: `.cursor/gates/execution/failure-recovery.md` â€” do not stop on first command failure
- Return completion fields: `deployment_url`, `deployment_status`, `dns_status`, `https_status`

## DON'T

- Deploy with failing build or tests
- Hardcode API tokens, Cloudflare credentials, or `.env` files in commits
- Autonomous agent production deploy without human-approved gates
- Respond instructions-only when tools and credentials are available â€” **execute** the pipeline
- Skip QA evidence before production ERP ship

## Environment Validation

Before deploy, verify:

- [ ] Secret store path exists (Windows: `%USERPROFILE%\.config\teknovo\secrets\`; Linux: `/root/.config/teknovo/secrets/`)
- [ ] Required env files present (e.g. `cloudflare.env`) â€” list missing paths, never print values
- [ ] Target branch/environment matches intent
- [ ] Build and test green on deploy branch

